In [7]:
def clean_up_keggs(keggs_list, delim = "("):
    return [kegg.split(delim)[0] for kegg in keggs_list]
In [8]:

import plotly.plotly as py
import plotly.graph_objs as go

import plotly.offline as offline
import plotly.plotly as py
from plotly.graph_objs import *




from plotly.offline import download_plotlyjs, init_notebook_mode, plot, iplot

offline.init_notebook_mode()


def return_trace(x_vals, y_vals, z_vals, kegg_names, trace_name, trace_size, 
                 color_vals, trace_width, alpha):

    trace = go.Scatter3d(
        x=x_vals,
        y=y_vals,
        z=z_vals,
        text = kegg_names,
        mode='markers',
        name = trace_name,
        marker=dict(
            size=trace_size,
            color = color_vals,
            symbol = 'circle',
            line=dict(
                color=color_vals,
                width=trace_width
            ),
            opacity=alpha
        )
    )
    
    return trace
